Document: RemoteTransform3D
Path: godot/classes/class_remotetransform3d.rst
Summary: RemoteTransform3D synchronizes its Transform3D to a remote Node3D using global or local coordinates.

RemoteTransform3D pushes its own Transform3D to another Node3D-derived node (called the remote node) in the scene. It can be configured to update the remote node's position, rotation, and/or scale. The synchronization can occur using either global coordinates (relative to the scene origin) or local coordinates (relative to the remote node's parent). This allows for precise control over how transformations are applied to the target node.
---CHUNK---
